body.description: Value and quality come together beautifully in the VIZIO V Series 50” class (49. 5" Diag.) 4K HDR, Smart TV. With a budget friendly combination of 4K resolution, High Dynamic Range, Smart TV apps, and Voice control compatibility with select devices, The V Series gives you the best features at the smartest value. With VIZIO’s award winning Full array LED backlighting, you’ll see the Difference in the clarity and detail of the picture of the all-new V Series. Ultra HD (3840×2160) resolution offers four times the detail of a 1080P TV, HD video is automatically upscale for the best possible picture, and the V Series TV is equipped to support high Dynamic Range for dazzling colors and contrast. Watch razor sharp 4K Ultra HD content from 4K formatted Blue ray movies, 4K enabled game consoles, and even shows streamed from apps like Netflix. You won't need a separate streaming device, as the V Series can easily stream your favorite shows from apps directly on the TV. And VIZIO watch free lets you stream over 100 channels Absolutely free – live news, movies, sports, comedy, music and more. Every VIZIO Smart TV also has Chromecast built in so you can stream entertainment from thousands of Chromecast enabled video and music apps right to the TV. And the V Series is ready for the future of TV – watch high Dynamic Range content Available through apps such as Netflix and Hulu, and turn on your TV or change channels with just your voice using Alexa or the Google Assistant supported devices like Google Home. The VIZIO V Series 4K HDR, Smart TV delivers what you love best about TV at an exceptional value.

reviews.reviewText: Great buy @$209.00 and it arrived a week early. No issues during shipment, set arrived in excellent condition. I was very skeptical about buying a tv online but after an exshausting search I gave in. Great experience.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 21, 2021
reviews.reviewTitle: 1.0 out of 5 stars Do Not Buy "Refurbished" TV from Amazon
reviews.reviewText: I bought this TV and had difficulties getting it to work from the start. After resetting the TV I was able to get it on and running and even watched a couple of movies. When I unplugged the TV to move it, the issue I had originally experienced happened again. The screen would show the Vizio logo then proceed to a black screen never loading to home. After I reset the TV to factory setting the second time, I was able to get it woking and even enjoyed it for a couple hours before turning it off. When I went to watch it again at night I was able to get to a movie but when I tried to play it the screen would go completely green and not show any sort of picture. I do not have any issue with wifi and have since bought a new Samsung that works perfectly fine in my room. I don't know what is wrong with this TV but I do not believe amazon does a thorough enough job when reselling there used TV's. I would not suggest buying anything but brand new TV's from this website.

reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Poor Remote/Good TV
reviews.reviewText: The TV is great! I love the picture and the adjustments that can be made. What I don't like is the remote. I'm hoping I can get a universal that will work with the TV that will allow me to stop or pause, rewind or advance a movie as I can with the Firestick. Otherwise, it's perfect for me. I would buy another...if I can replace the lame remote.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 30, 2021
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Good TV for price and looks absolutely stunning, but has some problems that people should know
reviews.reviewText: I got my TV about a week ago. When I got it, it all seemed perfect and great. Just had to mess with picture settings a little for HDR games and such. Jump to a few hours later, I just got done with some gaming and decided to watch something with the TV speakers instead of headphones. The audio wouldn’t play. It just kept making a small tick sound when it was supposed to play audio. Just one small tick and then nothing. Whenever I would power down the TV, it would make 5 ticks slowly and then stop and it would do the same when I turn it on. Still no audio. Tried resetting the TV and it did nothing. Randomly it started producing sound again after a while. Now it randomly does make sound and then randomly stops making sound and just does the small ticking. This makes it impossible to watch anything through the smart features because there is no sound. Luckily I have my Xbox and can just use headphones. But anybody who is hoping for just a smart TV to watch everything on should beware this.
